Section 1:
Act 637 of the Regular Session
1 State of Arkansas As Engrossed: H3/31/25
A Bill
2 95th General Assembly
3 Regular Session, 2025 HOUSE BILL 1677
4
5 By: Representatives Bentley, McGrew, Hawk
6 By: Senator J. Payton
7
For An Act To Be Entitled
8
9 AN ACT TO AUTHORIZE ALCOHOL AND DRUG ABUSE TREATMENT
10 PROGRAMS TO MAINTAIN EMERGENCY MEDICATION KITS; AND
11 FOR OTHER PURPOSES.
12
13
Subtitle
14
15 TO AUTHORIZE ALCOHOL AND DRUG ABUSE
16 TREATMENT PROGRAMS TO MAINTAIN EMERGENCY
17 MEDICATION KITS.
18
19 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF ARKANSAS:
20
21 SECTION 1. Arkansas Code Title 20, Chapter 64, Subchapter 9, is
22 amended to add an additional section to read as follows:
23 20-64-912. Emergency medication kits — Definition.
24 (a) As used in this section, "emergency medication kit" means a kit
25 containing medication that may be required for immediate therapeutic needs of
26 a patient and that are not available from any other source in sufficient time
27 to prevent risk of harm by delay.
28 (b)(1) An alcohol and drug abuse treatment program, including a stand-
29 alone detoxification facility or substance abuse treatment center, may
30 maintain an emergency medication kit if the alcohol and drug abuse treatment
31 program has a physician or other medical personnel on staff and is able to
32 administer the controlled substances and noncontrolled legend drugs.
33 (2)(A) The alcohol and drug abuse treatment program shall
34 designate one (1) licensed pharmacy to supply and oversee the emergency
35 medication kit.
36 (B) The licensed pharmacy under subdivision (b)(2)(A) of
*JMB463*
03-31-2025 12:18:10 JMB463
As Engrossed: H3/31/25 HB1677
1 this section shall be registered with the United States Drug Enforcement
2 Administration and licensed by the Arkansas State Board of Pharmacy.
3 (3) The emergency medication kit shall be:
4 (A) Stored in a locked container or cabinet behind a
5 locked door; and
6 (B) Accessible only to licensed medical personnel.
7 (4) The medication in the emergency medication kit shall only be
8 administered by licensed medical personnel acting on the order of a physician
9 or advanced practice registered nurse in compliance with 21 C.F.R. § 1306.11
10 and 21 C.F.R. § 1306.21.
11 (5) All drugs administered from the kit shall be replaced within
12 seventy-two (72) hours by the designated licensed pharmacy based on a
13 prescription for the patient to whom the drugs were administered.
14 (c) The Arkansas State Board of Pharmacy shall adopt rules regarding
15 the emergency medication kit, including without limitation:
16 (1) The contents of the emergency medication kit, which shall
17 not contain a Schedule II controlled substance;
18 (2) The quantity of each medication in the emergency medication
19 kit;
20 (3) The storage and security requirements for an emergency
21 medication kit; and
22 (4) The use and access of an emergency medication kit.
23
24 /s/Bentley
